  "prompt": "I am poor but I want to invest. What should I do?",
  "response": "Here are some strategies for investing with limited funds:\n\n1. Start small\n- Begin with whatever you can afford, even $5-$10 per month\n- Consistency is key\n\n2. Use low-cost investment platforms\n- Robinhood\n- Acorns\n- Betterment\n- Wealthfront\n\n3. Consider low-cost investment options\n- Index funds\n- Exchange-traded funds (ETFs)\n- Fractional shares\n- Retirement accounts like Roth IRA\n\n4. Automated savings\n- Set up automatic transfers to investment accounts\n- Use apps that round up purchases and invest spare change\n\n5. Learn and educate yourself\n- Read personal finance books\n- Follow investment blogs\n- Take free online courses\n\n6. Reduce expenses\n- Create a budget\n- Cut unnecessary spending\n- Save money to invest\n\n7. Side hustles\n- Use extra income for investments\n- Freelance\n- Part-time work\n\n8. Emergency fund first\n- Build 3-6 months of living expenses\n- Provides financial stability\n\n9. Retirement accounts\n- 401(k) with employer match\n- Traditional/Roth IRA\n\n10. Long-term perspective\n- Don't expect quick riches\n- Focus on gradual, consistent growth",
